{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, regarding (i), this seems to be the first uniqueness result for viscosity solutions of a mean-field PDE over an infinite dimensional state space (that we provide in terms of uniqueness of L-viscosity solutions of (1.5), i.e.",
    "in the sense of B-continuous viscosity solution of the \"lifted\" HJB (1.6)).",
    "Compared to the corresponding meanfield game problem in [57] where particles are modeled by abstract evolution equations on Hilbert spaces (or in [61] for mean-field games with delays rewritten as abstract evolution equations on Hilbert spaces) in the linear-quadratic setting, we consider general dynamics and cost functionals.",
    "Regarding (iii) and (iv), we remark that such properties are not easy to obtain even in the case H = R d and even in that setting there are very few results of this kind.",
    "Applications."
  ]
}